The Department and the Commissioner shall jointly:
Adopt regulations necessary to carry out the provisions of this subtitle consistent with § 1917(b) of the Social Security Act and any applicable federal guidelines;
On or before January 1, 2008, report to the General Assembly, in accordance with § 2-1246 of the State Government Article, on the implementation of the Program, including:
The number of long-term care policies approved by the Department for inclusion in the Program;
The measures undertaken to educate the public as required under § 15-406 of this subtitle; and
Any other information related to the implementation of the Program that the Department determines necessary; and
Beginning January 1, 2009, and on or before January 1 of each year thereafter, report to the General Assembly, in accordance with § 2-1246 of the State Government Article on:
The effectiveness of the Program;
The impact of the Program on State expenditures for medical assistance;
The number of enrollees in the Program; and
The number of long-term care policies offered in the State under the Program.
